{{short description|Adûnaic word}}
'''''pharaz''''' is an [[Adûnaic]] word meaning "[[gold]]".<ref>{{App|Consonants}}</ref><ref>{{SD|Nouns}}, p. 426</ref><ref>{{PE|17}}, p. 120</ref>
==Examples==
* ''[[Ar-Pharazôn#Etymology|Ar-Pharazôn]]''
==Etymology==
The similarity with the [[Khuzdul]] word ''[[baraz]]'' "red" has been noted; possibly ''pharaz'' represents an ancient [[Mannish]] loanword from the [[Dwarves]].<ref>{{PM|Dwarves}}</ref><ref>{{webcite|author=[[David Salo]]|articleurl=http://elfling.midgardsmal.com/index.php?topic=100505.0|articlename=Another Khuzdul Loanword in Adunaic?|website=Elfling}}</ref>
